theorem Topology.P1_closure_of_isOpen {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X}
    (hA : IsOpen A) : Topology.P1 (A := closure A) := by
  -- First establish the equality `closure (interior (closure A)) = closure A`.
  have h_eq : closure (interior (closure A)) = closure A := by
    -- One inclusion is immediate from monotonicity of `closure`.
    have h₁ : closure (interior (closure A)) ⊆ closure A :=
      closure_mono (interior_subset : interior (closure A) ⊆ closure A)
    -- For the other inclusion we use `closure A = closure (interior A)` (since `A` is open).
    have h₂ : closure A ⊆ closure (interior (closure A)) := by
      -- `closure A = closure (interior A)` for an open set `A`.
      have h_cl_eq : closure A = closure (interior A) :=
        (Topology.closureInterior_eq_closure_of_isOpen (A := A) hA).symm
      -- `interior A` is contained in `interior (closure A)`.
      have h_sub : interior A ⊆ interior (closure A) :=
        interior_mono subset_closure
      -- Taking closures preserves this inclusion.
      have h_cl_sub : closure (interior A) ⊆ closure (interior (closure A)) :=
        closure_mono h_sub
      simpa [h_cl_eq] using h_cl_sub
    exact subset_antisymm h₁ h₂
  -- Translate the equality of closures into the desired `P1` property.
  exact
    ((Topology.P1_iff_closureInterior_eq_closure (A := closure A)).2 h_eq)

theorem Topology.P1_closureInterior {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] (A : Set X) :
    Topology.P1 (A := closure (interior A)) := by
  dsimp [Topology.P1]
  intro x hx
  -- We show `closure (interior A) ⊆ closure (interior (closure (interior A)))`.
  have h_subset : closure (interior A) ⊆ closure (interior (closure (interior A))) := by
    -- First, `interior A ⊆ interior (closure (interior A))` by monotonicity of `interior`.
    have h_int : (interior A : Set X) ⊆ interior (closure (interior A)) := by
      have : (interior A : Set X) ⊆ closure (interior A) := Set.subset_closure
      exact interior_mono this
    -- Taking closures preserves inclusion.
    exact closure_mono h_int
  exact h_subset hx

theorem interior_closure_eq_univ_of_dense {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X]
    {A : Set X} (hA : Dense (A : Set X)) :
    interior (closure (A : Set X)) = (Set.univ : Set X) := by
  simpa [hA.closure_eq] using
    (by
      simp : interior (Set.univ : Set X) = (Set.univ : Set X))
